Most&nbsp;of the race, dying rabbits are there&nbsp;to be&nbsp;picked off, with&nbsp;much less pain&nbsp;experienced while doing it.<div>In a large race with many competitors, the first-time stealth racer can feel quite an&nbsp;adrenaline rush&nbsp;passing so many runners so quickly.</div><div>He may unwittingly speed up and wear himself out too soon.</div><div>But next time&nbsp;he tapers&nbsp;his reaction to savor the experience for the entire race.</div>